<body class="en">
  <main class="container">
    <h1 class="page-title">My Alarm Is Not Ringing</h1>

    <p class="lead">
      If your alarm does not ring or rings late, it is usually related to permissions or your device’s battery settings.
    </p>

    <p class="paragraph">
      On Android devices, alarm behavior can be affected by battery optimization, background activity restrictions,
      exact alarm permissions, Do Not Disturb settings, and other system settings.
    </p>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Check These First</h2>

      <ul class="list">
        <li>Make sure the alarm is turned on in the app.</li>
        <li>Make sure your device volume is not too low.</li>
        <li>Make sure notification permission is allowed. This is especially important.</li>
        <li>Make sure “Display over other apps” permission is allowed if the full-screen alarm does not appear.</li>
        <li>Check whether Do Not Disturb access is required.</li>
        <li>Set the app as an exception to battery optimization.</li>
        <li>Restart your device and try again.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Guide</h2>

      <p class="paragraph">
        In most cases, allowing the required permissions and adjusting battery settings will solve the problem.
      </p>

      <p class="paragraph">
        For stable alarm operation, this app may be affected by your device settings.
        We recommend checking the related settings when using the app for the first time.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</body>
</html>